This programs focus
Write a program that prompts for a file name, then opens that file and reads through the file, 
and print the contents of the file in upper case. Use the file words.txt to produce the output below.

# Use words.txt as the file name
fname = input("py.words.txt")
fh = open("words.txt" ,"r") # This phrase using the file in the Question descriping: "words.txt" , and read it
for line in fh: # Setting the loop, because we need to read every in each line
   line =line.rstrip()  # If we don't use rstrip(), in the end of each phrase the program will output the  blank  after reading each line 
   line =line.upper() # We transforme output from lower to  upper case.
   print(line)
